Fntastic. I made a few minor changes to the recipe (which I usually feel is cheating when you are rating a recipe) but since they are minor I feel as I did not compromise the orginal recipe. Here are the changes. I cut the breasts into large "chunks" and then sauteed. When I boiled the peppers to make the sauce I added a sprinkle of red pepper flakes. I served it over Orzo and topped it with crumbled Feta Cheese...not parsley.

Rating: 4
Just made this for dinner with 50% more of all ingredients (i.e., 3 Tbsp butter, 3 garlic, 1 1/2 cups of broth)...and it was delicious! Didn't have chicken broth so used beef and didn't have parsley. Added the onions as other reviewers suggested. The extra ingredients did give it more sauce as another reviewer suggested, and it was great! Would prefer the peppers a bit more crisp than mushy, but the taste was amazing!

Rating: 4
My family LOVED this! I used the package of three tri-color bell peppers from Trader Joe's (red, orange and yellow) and, per the other reviews, added thinly sliced red onion. I cooked the peppers and onion low-and-slow for about an hour or so. I think I'd double the peppers/onions next time because they were devoured quickly. Really, really good.

