Rating: 4
I made this early in the day today so I only had to cook noodles and nuke the chicken and sauce at suppertime. (The mercury was supposed to hit 100 degrees.) Done this way the kitchen stayed cooler than 80 degrees at 6 PM!! Since I was cooking for 2, I only used 2 breast halves, 1 orange and 1/2 red bell pepper, but I did make the amount of sauce written for 4 servings. Increased the garlic to 5 cloves, sprinkled the raw chicken with curry powder, added 1/8 tsp. crushed red pepper flakes, and thickened the sauce with flour/water (all are suggestions by reviewers--Thanks to all of you). I also added a splash of balsamic vinegar at the very end to give it a bit more zing. LOVED the sauce over noodles. VERY, VERY YUMMY. Will definitely make this many times!!! I couldn't really tell that the flavor of the bell peppers infused into the chicken, but the sauce was SO excellent, who cares???

Rating: 4
